# API Adapter Standards

## Architecture
Each provider = one adapter class inheriting BaseAdapter.
All in `backend/api/adapters/`.

## Rate Limits (enforce strictly)
| Provider          | Rate               | Auth             |
|-------------------|--------------------|------------------|
| OpenAlex          | 100 req/sec w/ key | api_key URL param|
| Semantic Scholar  | 100 req/sec w/ key | x-api-key header |
| Crossref          | 50 req/min         | mailto: header   |
| NIH RePORTER      | 1 req/sec          | none             |
| OSF               | reasonable         | none             |
| ClinicalTrials    | reasonable         | none             |

## Error Handling
- 429 Too Many Requests → exponential backoff (base 1s, max 60s, jitter)
- Inspect `x-ratelimit-remaining` header when available
- Log all API failures with request context

## Politeness
- Crossref: use "polite pool" by setting mailto in User-Agent
- NIH RePORTER: respect 1 req/sec — never burst
